    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix F1AP interface message loss due to incorrect throughputlog tick event handling\n\n### Summary\nThere is a F1AP interface handling error between CU and DU causing message loss or corruption downstream of function _tick_event in common/utils/T/tracer/logger/throughputlog.c. When calling _tick_event() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in _tick_event or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\nThis fix corrects the circular buffer management order and ensures proper timing of updating last_tick values.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/logger/throughputlog.c`: Fixed circular buffer management sequence in _tick_event function and repositioned last_tick_frame/subframe updates to prevent race conditions with data events.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy F1AP traffic between CU and DU, observe \"WARNING: throughputlog.c:45: data comes without previous tick!\" messages in the logs. This indicates that data events are arriving without a corresponding tick event being properly processed, leading to message loss or corruption in the F1AP interface handling.\n"
}